st}}\n\n{{disambiguation|surname}}\n", "name_user": "Oscxr Jx", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portal"}
{"title_page": "Rashmika Mandanna", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Indian actress and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rashmika Mandanna papu\n| caption            = Mandanna at the ''Dear Comrade'' Press Meet in 2019\n| image              = Rashmika Mandanna PYTV press meet.jpg\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|04|05}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Rashmika-Mandanna|title=Rashmika Mandanna: Movies, Photos, Videos, News & Biography \u2013 eTimes|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Virajpet]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|model}}\n| years_active       = 2016\u2013present\n}}\n'''Rashmika Mandanna''' (born 5 April 1996) is an Indian film actress and model who works predominantly in [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] films. She is popularly dubbed by the [[Mass media|media]] and [[Kannada film industry]] as the 'Karnataka Crush'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/metrolife/metrolife-on-the-move/the-outrage-against-rashmika-is-unnecessary-751971.html|title=The outrage against Rashmika is unnecessary|date=4 August 2019|website=Deccan Herald}}</ref><ref name=\"Rosh\">{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/amp_articleshow/63129397.cms|title=The Belageddu song from Kirik Party had you dubbed as the \u2018Karnataka Crush\u2019. Your reaction to that?|work=timesofindia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/articleshow/63129397.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna is the Bangalore Times Most Desirable Woman 2017 \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Rashmika is one among very few actresses to have a film gross \u20b91 billion in such a short span<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/sep/03/rashmika-mandanna-lands-in-crorepati-club-1866645.amp|title=Rashmika Mandanna lands in crorepati club|work=newindianexpress}}</ref> and one of the most popular and highest-paid actresses in [[Tollywood (Telugu)|Telugu]] and [[Kannada]] cinema industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-joins-the-big-league-of-highest-paid-female-actors-in-tollywood/articleshow/69533649.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna joins the big league of highest paid female actors in Tollywood - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/rashmika-mandana-becomes-one-sandalwood-s-highest-paid-women-actors-91985</ref>\n\nRashmika made her acting debut in [[Kannada]] 2016 film ''[[Kirik Party]]''. In 2017 she starred in two commercially successful films, ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' and ''[[Chamak]]''. Later she made her Telugu debut with romantic drama ''[[Chalo]]'' in 2018.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/chalo-week-1-box-office-collection-naga-shouryas-film-becomes-superhit-just-7-days-760085|title=Chalo week 1 box office collection: Naga Shourya's film becomes a superhit in just 7 days|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=10 February 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> In the same year, she starred in the [[romcom]] film ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'', which has become one of the highest profit earners in Telugu cinema, which earned her wide recognition.<ref name=\"Gf\">{{cite web|url=https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-total-box-office-collection-area-wise-distributors-earnings-theatrical-rights-783819|title=The total collections of Geetha Govindam have reached Rs 130 crore gross at the worldwide box office in its lifetime|work=ibtimes}}</ref> Her third Telugu venture was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''.<ref name=\"Dev\">{{cite web|url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://english.sakshi.com/entertainment/2018/10/15/devadas-final-collections-joins-50-crore-club|title=Devadas Final Collections: Joins 50 Crore Club|website=Webcache.googleusercontent.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> It marked her third consecutive successful film in the same year in [[Telugu film industry]] after achieving a first hat trick-hit in [[Kannada film industry]], established herself as one of the leading actresses of [[Language|Telugu and Kannada cinema]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/geetha-govindam-storms-box-office-enters-100-crore-club/articleshow/65571937.cms|title=Geetha Govindam box office collection: Vijay Deverakonda-Rashmika Mandanna starrer storms box-office, enters 100 crore club|work=ibtimes}}</ref>\n \nShe starred in the commercially successful films such as ''[[Kirik Party]]'' (2016), ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' (2017), ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' (2017), ''[[Chalo]]'' (2018), ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' (2018), ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'' (2019), ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'' (2020) and ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' (2020)<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-3-day-box-office-collection-nithiin-achieves-what-vijays-wfl-couldnt-813820</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-6-day-box-office-collection-mahesh-babus-sln-makes-100-recovery-811829|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru 6-day box office collection: Mahesh Babu's SLN makes 100% recovery|website=International Business Times|date=17 January 2020|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2018/before-rashmika-mandanna-these-actresses-were-trolled-for-sexist-reasons-275854.html|title=Before Rashmika Mandanna, These Actresses Were Trolled For Sexist Reasons|first=Roktim|last=Rajpal|date=31 July 2018|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The back to back success of films has made her one of the most sought-after actresses in [[Cinema of South India|south Indian film industry]].<ref>https://www.google.sakshi.com/amp/story/entertainment%252F2018%252F12%252F23%252Frashmika-nithiin-bheeshma-update</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRashmika Mandanna was born on 5 April 1996 as the elder daughter of Suman and Madan Mandanna in [[Virajpet]], a town in [[Kodagu district]] of [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna says it\u2019s all luck by chance|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2016/dec/20/rashmika-mandanna-says-its-all-luck-by-chance-1551322--1.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/sandalwood/200416/a-reel-virajpet-beauty.html|title=A reel Virajpet beauty|date=20 April 2016|work=www.deccanchronicle.com}}</ref> She did her schooling in Coorg Public School (COPS), Kodagu before she pursued [[pre-university course]] in Mysore Institute of commerce and arts, she has bachelor's degree in Psychology, Journalism and English Literature from [[Ramaiah Institute of Technology|Ramaiah college of Arts, Science and Commerce]], along with her studies she was doing modeling and appeared in a couple of advertisements.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/amp?params=LzIwMTcvMDcvMDQvNTk3NTk2|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpete|work=deccanherald}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRashmika got engaged to actor [[Rakshit Shetty]]. They began dating during making of ''Kirik Party'' and got engaged on 3 July 2017 in a private ceremony in her hometown of Virajpet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/620787/rakshit-rashmika-get-engaged-virajpet.html|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpet|date=4 July 2017|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> The couple mutually broke off their engagement in September 2018, citing compatibility issues.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/rashmika-mandanna-calls-off-engagement-with-rakshit-shetty-1335970-2018-09-09|title=Rashmika Mandanna calls of engagement with Rakshit Shetty|work=www.indiatoday.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRashmika began modelling in 2012. She won the [[Clean & Clear]] Fresh Face of India title the same year and was made the brand ambassador of [[Clean & Clear]]. Then she got the title of TVC in Lamode Bangalore's top model hunt 2013. Her pictures from the competition impressed the makers of the film ''[[Kirik Party]]'' who then cast her as the female lead for the film in early 2014. \n{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote = \"I was just 19 when I shot for the film. I am more like Saanvi (her character name) in real life, mature beyond my age; so it didn't feel tough.\"| source =\u2014 Rashmika shared her maiden flick ''[[Kirik Party]]'' experience.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dundoo |first1=Sangeetha Devi |title=Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s license to dream |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/rashmika-mandanna-talks-about-geetha-govindam-devadas-dear-comrade-and-how-cinema-has-changed-her-life/article24665502.ece |website=The Hindu |date=11 August 2018}}</ref>}} In an interview with ''[[The Times of India]]'', she recalled: \"The makers of Kirik Party saw a picture of mine from the Clean & Clear Fresh Face of India 2012 competition \u2014 one in which I was dancing during the college round \u2014 and approached me to act in the film. So, it really got things going. I always wanted to be in films.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-on-her-debut/articleshow/56137743.cms|title=Meet Saanvi, the hottie from Kirik Party|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> She was cast as Saanvi Joseph, a college-goer, and the love interest of Karna (played by [[Rakshit Shetty]]).\n\n===Kannada debut and breakthrough (2016\u201317)===\nRashmika made her debut with ''[[Kirik Party]]'' in 2016, which opened to widespread acclaim from critics and audiences alike and went on to become [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing film]] of the year by collecting \u20b950 [[crore]]<ref name=\"ittt\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party dubbed by malayalam movie premam and Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|publisher=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> against production budget \u20b94 crore,<ref name=th>{{cite web|title=The budget of \u2018Kirik Party\u2019 would be around \u20b94crore|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/rakshith-shettys-kirik-party-to-go-on-the-floors-in-march/article8191273.ece\n|work=The Hindu}}</ref> and completed 150-days in main centers of [[Karnataka]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/krik-party-rakshit-shetty-rashmika-mandanna-celebrate-150-days-981176-2017-06-06|title=Kirik Party completes 150 days: Rakshit Shetty, Rashmika Mandanna celebrate with fans|website=India Today}}</ref> alongside Rashmika's performance received praise for her performance as Saanvi. The writer Sunayana Suresh of ''[[The Times of India]]'' states that \"Rashmika Mandanna as Saanvi is easy that pin-up girl in college and she breathes her path.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/kirik-party/movie-review/56250634.cms|title=Kirik Party Movie Review|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The film's reviewer for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' wrote, \"Rashmika Mandanna has outshone in the film along with the main character\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2016/dec/31/youngsters-live-the-kirik-life-here-1554624--2.html|title=Youngsters Live The Kirik Life Here|work=The New Indian Express|date=31 December 2016}}</ref> The ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]''`s Shashiprasad noted that \"Beautiful senior Saanvi played by Rashmika Mandanna, her beautiful and cute portrayal of Saanvi will surely remind all the guys their unforgettable crush from college days.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/301216/kirik-party-movie-review-watch-with-your-college-friends-for-maximum-fun.html|title=Kirik Party movie review: Watch with your college friends for maximum fun|work=\ndeccanchronicle}}</ref> This won her [[SIIMA|SIIMA Award for the Best Debut Actress]].<ref name=\"kirik\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/today/siima-2017awards-kannada.html|title=SIIMA 2017 Kannada winners list&nbsp;\u2014 idlebrain.com news|work=Idlebrain}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Rashmika's first release was [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]'s ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' opposite [[Puneeth Rajkumar]], which ran for 50-days in some theatres of [[Karnataka]].<ref>https://twitter.com/AppuFc007/status/960142093074161665?s=19</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s Sunayana Suresh wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna as cute as the leading lady and shows that she has comic timing that can be tapped in to.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/anjaniputhraa/amp_movie_review/62192278.cms|title=Anjaniputra review|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Cineloka'''s writer stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna as his love interest plays a good-natured, jaunty girl next door and delivers good performance.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cineloka.co.in/index.php/2017-04-23-04-49-47/movie-reviews/461-anjaniputra-movie-review-cineloka|title=AnjaniPutra Movie Review|work=Cineloka}}</ref>\nThe ''[[New Indian Express]]''`s Sharadhaa claimed that \"This is Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s first movie with Puneeth and she has upped her glam quotient, even while keeping her girl-next-door appeal.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/22/anjaniputra-review-this-film-is-for-puneeths-fans-by-a-fan-1734806.amp|title=Anjaniputra' Review|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> it earned her [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadati award for Best Actress]] and [[Awards|Luv lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]].<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-hemmeya-kannadathi-kannada-movie-news-kannada-news-208608</ref><ref>https://www.savasher.com/celebrity-actress/rashmika-mandanna-family-wiki-husband/</ref>\n\nHer next and last release was ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' opposite [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]], which ran for 100-days in a couple of theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitraloka.com/news/17333-chamak-completes-100-days.html|title='CHAMAK' COMPLETES 100 DAYS|work=chitraloka}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/chamak-world-television-premiere-on-saturday/articleshow/64872482.cms|title=Chamak world television premiere on Saturday \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Chamak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/chamak-is-in-safe-zone-kannada_amp-news-204535&ved|title=Chamak is in safe zone-Kannada  Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz}}</ref>\nshe receives critical acclaim from critics for her role as Khushi, ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer Sunayana Suresh stated that \"Rashmika has done a good job at ensuring the audience are with them throughout\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/chamak/amp_movie_review/62294436.cms|title=#Chamak Movie Review {3.5/5}: Critic Review of #Chamak by Times of India|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nWhile ''[[Bangalore Mirror]]''`s writer Shyam Prasad claimed that \"Rashmika sparkles in acting.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/reviews/chamak-movie-review-freshly-old-but-charming-enough/articleshow/62300173.cms|title=Chamak movie review: Freshly old, but charming enough|author=Shyam Prasad|website=Bangalore Mirror|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> ''[[The New Indian Express]]''`s \nSharadhaa wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna emerges as a good artiste in her third outing. The actress, who comes in two shades has taken responsibility for her character, and it shows.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/30/chamak-review-a-fresh-take-on-love-1740026.html|title='Chamak' review: A Fresh Take on Love|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> Latter garnered her first nomination for [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada]] at [[65th Filmfare Awards South]]. three consecutive films in [[Kannada]] language all succeeded at the box office makes her 'hat-trick' heroine in [[Kannada film industry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-mandanna-heroine-of-2017-kannada-news-204253|title=Rashmika Mandanna heroine of 2017 \u2013 Kannada Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz.com}}</ref>\n\n===Debut and fame in Telugu: 2018===\n[[File:Rashmikamandanna.jpg|right|175px|thumb|Rashmika during an inauguration of Mugda Arts Store at [[Hyderabad]] in 2018]]\nShe made her [[Telugu cinema|Telugu film]] debut opposite [[Naga Shourya]] with the film titled ''[[Chalo]]''.,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna \u2019s tollywood debut with Naga Shourya|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/mar/16/rashmika-mandanna-s-tollywood-debut-with-naga-shourya-1581751.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=16 March 2017}}</ref> which ran for 100-days in some theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/chalo-7-days-worldwide-collections-naga-shaurya-starrer-rakes-in-share-of-rs-8-cr/amp_articleshow/62873123.cms|title=Chalo 7 days\u2019 worldwide collections: Naga Shaurya starrer rakes in share of Rs 8 cr  \u2013 Times of India|website=Timesofindia.com}}</ref> critics have been heaped praise on Rashmika for her performance.<ref name=\"Chal\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/> The ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s Hemanth Kumar wrote that \"Rashmika makes a terrific debut and she\u2019s a joy to watch on screen\".<ref name=\"Chal\">{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/chalo-movie-review-naga-shaurya-rashmika-mandanna-stand-out-in-this-quirky-comedy-4333869.html|title=Chalo movie review: Naga Shaurya, Rashmika Mandanna stand out in this quirky comedy- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=3 February 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> While writer of ''[[The Hindu]]''`s Srivathsan Nadadhur stated that she makes a \"Confident debut\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/chalo-review-being-fair-in-love-and-war/article22634327.ece|title='Chalo' review: Being fair in love and war|first=Srivathsan|last=Nadadhur|date=2 February 2018|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''Idlebrain'''s Jeevi   \nnoted that she was \"very cute and acts well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/chalo.html|title=Chalo review by jeevi \u2013 Telugu cinema review \u2013 Naga Shaurya and Rashmika Mandanna|website=Idlebrain.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Greatandra'' stated that \"Kannada heroine Rashmika is cute.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.greatandhra.com/movies/reviews/chalo-review-fun-factor-works-out-87269|title=Chalo, Chalo Rating, Chalo Review, Chalo Telugu Review, Naga Shaurya|first=|last=Venkat|date=2 February 2018|website=greatandhra.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The ''123Telugu'' stated that \"Rashmika makes an impressive debut and suits perfectly in her role.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/chalo-telugu-movie-review.html|title=Chalo Telugu Movie Review|date=3 February 2018|website=123telugu.com}}</ref> ''Telugu360'''s editor wrote that \"Rashmika lent good support to Shaurya with her performance. She is bubbly and effervescent in comedy scenes and shows good promise as an actress.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telugu360.com/chalo-movie-review/|title=Chalo Movie Review, Chalo Review Naga Shourya Chalo movie review|date=2 February 2018|website=Telugu360.com}}</ref>\n\nHer next film was ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to positive reviews and went on to collect over \u20b9130 [[crore]]<ref name=\"Gf\"/> against production budget \u20b95 crore and ran for 100-days in couple of theatres.<ref name=\"Geetha\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-box-office-collection-day-8-vijay-starrer-sets-cash-registers-ringing-bakrid-778539 |title=Geetha Govindam is a small budget movie that is made on a shoe-string budget of \u20b95 crore |work=ibtimes.co.in |access-date=23 August 2018}}</ref> \nand brought her much recognition, making her very popular in [[Telangana]] and [[Andhra Pradesh]], alongside she received immense critical appraisal from both critics and audience, ''[[Hindustan Times]]''`s Priyanka Sundar noted that \"Rashmika have taken this solid plot a notch higher with their delightful performances. Rashmika especially will have you rooting for her throughout the film\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-will-win-you-over-in-this-rom-com/story-yUxgQ8qPoaczB4Bra6IYzO.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda, Rashmika Mandanna will win you over in this rom-com|date=15 August 2018|website=M.hindustantimes.com}}</ref> The writer of ''[[The Times of India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika too sparkles and the scenes between the two is what makes Geetha Govindam so likeable\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/geetha-govindam/movie-review/65411950.cms|title=Geetha Govindam Review {3.5/5}: If you love rom-coms, you're going to lap this up. A big thumbs up!|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref> ''[[The Indian Express]]'' claimed that \"Rashmika as uncompromising Geetha also does a pretty good job\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-5308099/|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda starrer is a charming romantic comedy|date=15 August 2018|website=Indianexpress.com}}</ref> ''[[The Hindu]]'' stated that \"She has an easy screen presence and the potential to handle more well-written parts\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/geetha-govindam-review-this-vijay-deverakonda-film-is-an-antithesis-to-arjun-reddy/article24696712.ece|title='Geetha Govindam' review: The good guy takes over|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|date=15 August 2018|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika and Vijay, who makes it an enjoyable watch. Being paired on-screen for the first time, they  performed their respective roles very well.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakondas-performance-proves-he-is-not-a-one-hit-wonder-4970831.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda's performance proves he is not a one hit wonder- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=15 August 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rashmika mandanna at the Promotions of Devadas.png|right|150px|thumb|Rashmika at promotion of ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'' movie in 2018]]\nHer next release was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'', she shared a space with [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]] and [[Nani (actor)|Nani]] as one of the main lead in the film along [[Akanksha Singh]]. It marked her hat-trick hit film in her career in [[Telugu film industry]] according to few regional reliable sources. She had less screen space, though received critical appraisal for her performance. ''Chitramala''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika Mandanna impressed in her role and made her presence felt.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitramala.in/devadas-telugu-movie-review-276459.html/amp|title=Devadas Telugu Movie Review|date=27 September 2018|website=Chitramala.in}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer states that \"Rashmika deserved better character arc, even though she plays a people of prominence.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/devadas/movieshow/65977659.cms|title=Devadas Movie Review {3.5/5}: The Deva and Das show is thoroughly entertaining|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Continued success and Tamil debut (2019-20) ===\nRashmika started 2019 acting in ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'', Kannada language film opposite [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]], which received decent reviews from the both audience and critics upon the release. And began earning a profit within five-days of its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/yajamana-box-office-collection-darshans-film-profit-zone-just-5-days-end-1st-week-high-note-793347|title=Yajamana box office collection: Darshan's film in profit zone in just 5 days, to end 1st week on high note|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|date=7 March 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Later it collected over \u20b950 crore<ref name=\"Yajj\"/> against production budget \u20b918 crore<ref name=\"Dar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2019/yajamana-day-14-box-office-collection-darshan-continues-to-rule-in-karnataka-slow-run-in-the-us-283815.html|title=Yajamana Day 14 Box Office Collection \u2013 Darshan Continues To Rule In Karnataka But Slow Run In The US \u2013 Filmibeat|date=14 March 2019|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> and ran for over 100-days in some theatres in [[Karnataka]].<ref name=\"Yajj\">{{cite web|url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/entertainment/yajamana-grosses-rs-50-crore-becomes-darshan-s-first-movie-to-cross-the-mark-kgf-rajakumara-the-villain-pod1xd|title=Yajamana grosses Rs 50 crore, becomes Darshan's first movie to cross the mark|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>Darshan's Yajamana hits the 100-day mark - https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/darshans-yajamana-hits-the-100-day-mark/articleshow/69375318.cms</ref>\nShe has been received critical acclaim for her performance as Kaveri, ''[[Times Of India]]'' editor claimed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is cute and her pairing with Darshan works well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/yajamana/movie-review/68213387.cms|title=Yajamana Review {3.5/5}: A must-watch for fans of commercial cinema|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> The ''[[New Indian Express]]'' editor noticed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is allicient as the love interest and justifies the village girl\u2019s character\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2019/mar/02/yajamana-review-this-darshan-starrer-is-a-mass-entertainer-with-social-message-1945439.amp|title='Yajamana' review: This Darshan-starrer is a mass entertainer with social message - The New Indian Express|website=www.newindianexpress.com}}</ref> In 2019, her next film was ''[[Dear Comrade]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to mixed reviews from  both critics and audience. It went on to become a financial failure and touted as first flop at box office in Rashmika's film career. Even though she received overwhelming critical acclaim for her performance in the film as 'Lilly'.<ref>https://www.tollywood.net/article/dear-comrade-to-face-50-loss-in-ceded-huge-disaster/49355/amp</ref> It earned her first [[Award|behindwood's gold medal award]] for best actor critics choice.<ref name=\" BG\">https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/winners-of-7th-behindwoods-gold-medals/rashmika-mandanna-behindwoods-gold-medal-winner-2019.html</ref> She has gone on to win awards honouring her cinematic contributions, including ''Just for Women'''s Magazine \"Sensation of the Year Award\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jfwonline.com/article/the-future-of-cinema-rashmika-mandanna/|title=The future of cinema; Rashmika Mandanna|website=JFW Just for women|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> and the \"Youth Icon\" award in [[Colors Tamil]]'s \"Wonder Women\" Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijays-wife-ajiths-viswasam-director-rashmika-keerthy-suresh-celebs-wonder-women-awards-807492|title=From Vijay's wife to Ajith's Viswasam director, Rashmika Mandanna to Keerthy Suresh, celebs galore at WW Awards|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|date=21 October 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=english|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> She was invited to participate in a panel discussion (\"Leading Actress\") at the 2019 [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]] (the award function's Golden Jubilee) along with [[Nithya Menen]] moderated by the Indian film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]], which was organized in [[Goa]].<ref>https://www.filmibeat.com/interviews/iffi-2019-kannada-actress-rashmika-mandanna-interview-exclusive-filmibeat-292252.html\n</ref>\n\nIn 2020 Rashmika starred opposite [[Mahesh Babu]] in ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'', which opened to decent reviews from audience and critics upon the release and went on to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing films]] in the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industry,<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-9-day-box-office-collection-anil-ravipudi-scores-career-best-mahesh-babu-811970</ref> and emerged as Rashmika's career highest profit erner to date by collecting \u20b92 billion in just 10-days.<ref name=\"SLN\">https://www.businesstoday.in/trending/box-office/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-film-ahead-of-mahesh-babu-sarileru-neekevvaru/story/394286.html</ref><ref name=\"SLN 1st week collection\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/sankranti-telugu-releases-ala-vaikuntapuramloo-sarileru-neekevvaru-strike-gold-at-the-box-office/story-Bm8033vi57uLu8fTVHkqJK.html|title=Sankranti Telugu releases Ala Vaikuntapuramloo, Sarileru Neekevvaru strike gold at the box office|website=Hindustan Times|date=20 January 2020|access-date=21 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 3 Days\">{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/mahesh-babu-film-sarileru-neekevvaru-earns-rs-103-crore-6216179/|title=Mahesh Babu film Sarileru Neekevvaru earns Rs 103 crore|website=Indian Express|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-collection-mahesh-babu-and-rashmika-mandanna-starrer-hits-the-100-crore-mark-in-three-days/articleshow/73247929.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Box-Office Collection: Mahesh Babu and Rashmika Mandanna starrer hits the 100-crore mark in three days|website=The Times of India|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> And went on to collect over \u20b92.6 billion in 50-days theatrical run at worldwide box office.<ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection The Statesman\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/southern_cinema/sarileru-neekevvaru-mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-box-office-1502861238.html|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru: Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days at box office. It has grossed Rs 260 crore till now|website=[[The Statesman (India)|The Statesman]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection India TV\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/regional-cinema/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-593698|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of Sarileru Neekevvaru at box office|website=[[India TV]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection Outlook India\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-of-sarileru-neekevvaru-at-box-office/1747919|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of ''Sarileru Neekevvaru'' at box office|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> The reviewer of ''[[Times Of India]]'' Neeshita Nyayapati, stated \"Rashmika Mandanna woos, gets hyper, dances, has a catch-line, all for the male lead, but why she exists in this tale, other than to fawn over him is a mystery.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru/movie-review/73198148.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=The Times of India|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> The editor of ''[[India Today]]'' Janani K, claimed that \"We see Rashmika playing a typical 'loosu ponnu' (read: A mindless heroine who acts like a kid) who keeps stalking Mahesh Babu.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-mahesh-babu-film-is-utterly-disappointing-1635966-2020-01-11|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=India Today|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> Whereas, the editor of ''[[Hans India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna has impressed with her performance.\"<ref>https://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527\nhttps://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527</ref> Her next Telugu film in 2020 was ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' opposite [[Nithiin]], which opened to positive response from the both critics and audience.<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-813649\n</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/bheeshma-box-office-nithiins-highest-opening-in-the-telugu-states/articleshow/74253897.cms</ref> The film went on to become a financial hit at worldwide box office by collecting over \u20b950 crore.<ref>https://telugu.news18.com/news/movies/nithiin-bheeshma-movie-collects-50-crore-gross-world-wide-for-first-week-sr-464782.html</ref><ref>https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/nithiin-and-rashmika-starrer-bheeshma-movie-collects-rs-50-crores-gross-world-wind/articleshow/74391410.cms</ref> She received praise for her performance as Chaitra. The ''[[Firstpost]]'''s editor Hemanth Kumar praised her chemistry with Nithiin.<ref>https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bheeshma-movie-review-nithiin-rashmika-mandannas-romantic-drama-is-a-breezy-entertainer-8070741.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!Year!! Films !! Roles !! Director(s) !! Languages \n!Notes\n|-\n|2016\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| Saanvi Joseph\n| [[Rishab Shetty]]\n|rowspan='3'|[[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n|Kannada Debut and first film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| Kushi\n| [[Suni (director)|Suni]]\n|Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Kannada]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chalo]]''\n| L. Karthika\n| Venky Kudumula\n| rowspan='3'|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Telugu Debut\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]\n|Won \u2013 [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress (Critics) - Telugu]]<br />Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''\n| Inspector Pooja\n| Sriram Aditya\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n!scope=\"row\" |''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]''\n| Kaveri\n|[[Pon Kumaran]] <br> [[V. Harikrishna]]\n|[[Kannada]]\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  |''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n| Lilly\n| [[Bharat Kamma]]\n|rowspan='3'|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2020\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]''\n|Samskruthi\n|[[Anil Ravipudi]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]''\n|Chaitra\n|Venky Kudumula\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/bheeshma-nithiin-rashmika-mandanna-wraps-up-the-first-schedule-of-their-upcoming-film/articleshow/70429744.cms|title=Bheeshma: Nithiin, Rashmika Mandanna wraps up the first schedule of their upcoming film - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/bheeshma-to-arrive-on-feb-21-603864|title='Bheeshma' to arrive on Feb 21|last=India|first=The Hans|date=9 February 2020|website=www.thehansindia.com|language=en|access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#ffc;\"|''[[Pogaru]]'' {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|[[Nanda Kishore]]\n|[[Kannada]]\n|Filming<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/05/rashmika-mandanna-checks-into-dhruva-sarja-starrer-pogaru-1894325.html|title=Rashmika Mandanna checks into Dhruva Sarja-starrer 'Pogaru'|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref> (Dubbing Stage)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/nov/28/dhruva-sarja-to-resume-work-for-pogaru-15751.html|title=Dhruva Sarja to resume work for Pogaru|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[Sultan (2020 film)|Sultan]]'' {{dagger}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|Bakkiyaraj Kannan\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n|Post-production, Tamil Debut<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/karthis-sultan-to-hit-screens-during-summer-holidays/articleshow/73297255.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sultan-rashmika-mandanna-confirms-the-title-of-her-next-film-with-karthi-1581520-2019-08-16|title=Sultan: Rashmika Mandanna confirms the title of her next film with Karthi|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019|agency=Ist}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[Pushpa (film)|Pushpa]] ''{{dagger}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|[[Sukumar (director)|Sukumar]]\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Filming\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Language\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| [[South Indian International Movie Awards|South Indian International Movie Awards for Best Debut Actress (Leading Role)]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" | [[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Utsavam|IIFA Utsavam Award for Best Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2018\n| [[Awards|Luv Lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadathi Award for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Awards South for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|South Indian International Movie Awards for Bes]]\n[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|t Actress in Leading Role]]\n|-\n|[[Awards|TSR TV9 National Award for Best Actress]] \n|{{Nominated}} \n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n|[[Filmibeat|Filmibeat Award for Best Debutant Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|''[[Chalo]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards|Zee Cine Awards for Favorite Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Sri Kala Sudha Telugu Awards for Best Debut Heroine]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award for Best Actress]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Award|JFW award - Sensational Actor]]\n|{{Won}}<ref>VBJ JFW Awards 2019: Yet Another Unforgettable Success! https://jfwonline.com/article/vbj-jfw-awards-2019-yet-another-unforgettable-success/</ref>\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Awards South Best Actress Critics Choice]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Behindwoods Gold Medal (Best Actor Critics Choice)]]\n|''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n|{{Won}}<ref name=\"BG\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Rashmika Mandanna}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=8612305|title=Rashmika Mandanna}}\n\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Female D\u00e9butante}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Kodava people]]\n[[Category:People from Kodagu district]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Indian actress and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rashmika Mandanna\n| caption            = Mandanna at the ''Dear Comrade'' Press Meet in 2019\n| image              = Rashmika Mandanna PYTV press meet.jpg\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|04|05}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Rashmika-Mandanna|title=Rashmika Mandanna: Movies, Photos, Videos, News & Biography \u2013 eTimes|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Virajpet]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|model}}\n| years_active       = 2016\u2013present\n}}\n'''Rashmika Mandanna''' (born 5 April 1996) is an Indian film actress and model who works predominantly in [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] films. She is popularly dubbed by the [[Mass media|media]] and [[Kannada film industry]] as the 'Karnataka Crush'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/metrolife/metrolife-on-the-move/the-outrage-against-rashmika-is-unnecessary-751971.html|title=The outrage against Rashmika is unnecessary|date=4 August 2019|website=Deccan Herald}}</ref><ref name=\"Rosh\">{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/amp_articleshow/63129397.cms|title=The Belageddu song from Kirik Party had you dubbed as the \u2018Karnataka Crush\u2019. Your reaction to that?|work=timesofindia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/articleshow/63129397.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna is the Bangalore Times Most Desirable Woman 2017 \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Rashmika is one among very few actresses to have a film gross \u20b91 billion in such a short span<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/sep/03/rashmika-mandanna-lands-in-crorepati-club-1866645.amp|title=Rashmika Mandanna lands in crorepati club|work=newindianexpress}}</ref> and one of the most popular and highest-paid actresses in [[Tollywood (Telugu)|Telugu]] and [[Kannada]] cinema industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-joins-the-big-league-of-highest-paid-female-actors-in-tollywood/articleshow/69533649.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna joins the big league of highest paid female actors in Tollywood - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/rashmika-mandana-becomes-one-sandalwood-s-highest-paid-women-actors-91985</ref>\n\nRashmika made her acting debut in [[Kannada]] 2016 film ''[[Kirik Party]]''. In 2017 she starred in two commercially successful films, ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' and ''[[Chamak]]''. Later she made her Telugu debut with romantic drama ''[[Chalo]]'' in 2018.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/chalo-week-1-box-office-collection-naga-shouryas-film-becomes-superhit-just-7-days-760085|title=Chalo week 1 box office collection: Naga Shourya's film becomes a superhit in just 7 days|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=10 February 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> In the same year, she starred in the [[romcom]] film ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'', which has become one of the highest profit earners in Telugu cinema, which earned her wide recognition.<ref name=\"Gf\">{{cite web|url=https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-total-box-office-collection-area-wise-distributors-earnings-theatrical-rights-783819|title=The total collections of Geetha Govindam have reached Rs 130 crore gross at the worldwide box office in its lifetime|work=ibtimes}}</ref> Her third Telugu venture was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''.<ref name=\"Dev\">{{cite web|url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://english.sakshi.com/entertainment/2018/10/15/devadas-final-collections-joins-50-crore-club|title=Devadas Final Collections: Joins 50 Crore Club|website=Webcache.googleusercontent.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> It marked her third consecutive successful film in the same year in [[Telugu film industry]] after achieving a first hat trick-hit in [[Kannada film industry]], established herself as one of the leading actresses of [[Language|Telugu and Kannada cinema]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/geetha-govindam-storms-box-office-enters-100-crore-club/articleshow/65571937.cms|title=Geetha Govindam box office collection: Vijay Deverakonda-Rashmika Mandanna starrer storms box-office, enters 100 crore club|work=ibtimes}}</ref>\n \nShe starred in the commercially successful films such as ''[[Kirik Party]]'' (2016), ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' (2017), ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' (2017), ''[[Chalo]]'' (2018), ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' (2018), ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'' (2019), ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'' (2020) and ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' (2020)<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-3-day-box-office-collection-nithiin-achieves-what-vijays-wfl-couldnt-813820</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-6-day-box-office-collection-mahesh-babus-sln-makes-100-recovery-811829|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru 6-day box office collection: Mahesh Babu's SLN makes 100% recovery|website=International Business Times|date=17 January 2020|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2018/before-rashmika-mandanna-these-actresses-were-trolled-for-sexist-reasons-275854.html|title=Before Rashmika Mandanna, These Actresses Were Trolled For Sexist Reasons|first=Roktim|last=Rajpal|date=31 July 2018|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The back to back success of films has made her one of the most sought-after actresses in [[Cinema of South India|south Indian film industry]].<ref>https://www.google.sakshi.com/amp/story/entertainment%252F2018%252F12%252F23%252Frashmika-nithiin-bheeshma-update</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRashmika Mandanna was born on 5 April 1996 as the elder daughter of Suman and Madan Mandanna in [[Virajpet]], a town in [[Kodagu district]] of [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna says it\u2019s all luck by chance|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2016/dec/20/rashmika-mandanna-says-its-all-luck-by-chance-1551322--1.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/sandalwood/200416/a-reel-virajpet-beauty.html|title=A reel Virajpet beauty|date=20 April 2016|work=www.deccanchronicle.com}}</ref> She did her schooling in Coorg Public School (COPS), Kodagu before she pursued [[pre-university course]] in Mysore Institute of commerce and arts, she has bachelor's degree in Psychology, Journalism and English Literature from [[Ramaiah Institute of Technology|Ramaiah college of Arts, Science and Commerce]], along with her studies she was doing modeling and appeared in a couple of advertisements.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/amp?params=LzIwMTcvMDcvMDQvNTk3NTk2|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpete|work=deccanherald}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRashmika got engaged to actor [[Rakshit Shetty]]. They began dating during making of ''Kirik Party'' and got engaged on 3 July 2017 in a private ceremony in her hometown of Virajpet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/620787/rakshit-rashmika-get-engaged-virajpet.html|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpet|date=4 July 2017|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> The couple mutually broke off their engagement in September 2018, citing compatibility issues.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/rashmika-mandanna-calls-off-engagement-with-rakshit-shetty-1335970-2018-09-09|title=Rashmika Mandanna calls of engagement with Rakshit Shetty|work=www.indiatoday.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRashmika began modelling in 2012. She won the [[Clean & Clear]] Fresh Face of India title the same year and was made the brand ambassador of [[Clean & Clear]]. Then she got the title of TVC in Lamode Bangalore's top model hunt 2013. Her pictures from the competition impressed the makers of the film ''[[Kirik Party]]'' who then cast her as the female lead for the film in early 2014. \n{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote = \"I was just 19 when I shot for the film. I am more like Saanvi (her character name) in real life, mature beyond my age; so it didn't feel tough.\"| source =\u2014 Rashmika shared her maiden flick ''[[Kirik Party]]'' experience.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dundoo |first1=Sangeetha Devi |title=Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s license to dream |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/rashmika-mandanna-talks-about-geetha-govindam-devadas-dear-comrade-and-how-cinema-has-changed-her-life/article24665502.ece |website=The Hindu |date=11 August 2018}}</ref>}} In an interview with ''[[The Times of India]]'', she recalled: \"The makers of Kirik Party saw a picture of mine from the Clean & Clear Fresh Face of India 2012 competition \u2014 one in which I was dancing during the college round \u2014 and approached me to act in the film. So, it really got things going. I always wanted to be in films.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-on-her-debut/articleshow/56137743.cms|title=Meet Saanvi, the hottie from Kirik Party|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> She was cast as Saanvi Joseph, a college-goer, and the love interest of Karna (played by [[Rakshit Shetty]]).\n\n===Kannada debut and breakthrough (2016\u201317)===\nRashmika made her debut with ''[[Kirik Party]]'' in 2016, which opened to widespread acclaim from critics and audiences alike and went on to become [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing film]] of the year by collecting \u20b950 [[crore]]<ref name=\"ittt\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party dubbed by malayalam movie premam and Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|publisher=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> against production budget \u20b94 crore,<ref name=th>{{cite web|title=The budget of \u2018Kirik Party\u2019 would be around \u20b94crore|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/rakshith-shettys-kirik-party-to-go-on-the-floors-in-march/article8191273.ece\n|work=The Hindu}}</ref> and completed 150-days in main centers of [[Karnataka]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/krik-party-rakshit-shetty-rashmika-mandanna-celebrate-150-days-981176-2017-06-06|title=Kirik Party completes 150 days: Rakshit Shetty, Rashmika Mandanna celebrate with fans|website=India Today}}</ref> alongside Rashmika's performance received praise for her performance as Saanvi. The writer Sunayana Suresh of ''[[The Times of India]]'' states that \"Rashmika Mandanna as Saanvi is easy that pin-up girl in college and she breathes her path.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/kirik-party/movie-review/56250634.cms|title=Kirik Party Movie Review|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The film's reviewer for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' wrote, \"Rashmika Mandanna has outshone in the film along with the main character\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2016/dec/31/youngsters-live-the-kirik-life-here-1554624--2.html|title=Youngsters Live The Kirik Life Here|work=The New Indian Express|date=31 December 2016}}</ref> The ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]''`s Shashiprasad noted that \"Beautiful senior Saanvi played by Rashmika Mandanna, her beautiful and cute portrayal of Saanvi will surely remind all the guys their unforgettable crush from college days.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/301216/kirik-party-movie-review-watch-with-your-college-friends-for-maximum-fun.html|title=Kirik Party movie review: Watch with your college friends for maximum fun|work=\ndeccanchronicle}}</ref> This won her [[SIIMA|SIIMA Award for the Best Debut Actress]].<ref name=\"kirik\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/today/siima-2017awards-kannada.html|title=SIIMA 2017 Kannada winners list&nbsp;\u2014 idlebrain.com news|work=Idlebrain}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Rashmika's first release was [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]'s ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' opposite [[Puneeth Rajkumar]], which ran for 50-days in some theatres of [[Karnataka]].<ref>https://twitter.com/AppuFc007/status/960142093074161665?s=19</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s Sunayana Suresh wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna as cute as the leading lady and shows that she has comic timing that can be tapped in to.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/anjaniputhraa/amp_movie_review/62192278.cms|title=Anjaniputra review|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Cineloka'''s writer stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna as his love interest plays a good-natured, jaunty girl next door and delivers good performance.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cineloka.co.in/index.php/2017-04-23-04-49-47/movie-reviews/461-anjaniputra-movie-review-cineloka|title=AnjaniPutra Movie Review|work=Cineloka}}</ref>\nThe ''[[New Indian Express]]''`s Sharadhaa claimed that \"This is Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s first movie with Puneeth and she has upped her glam quotient, even while keeping her girl-next-door appeal.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/22/anjaniputra-review-this-film-is-for-puneeths-fans-by-a-fan-1734806.amp|title=Anjaniputra' Review|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> it earned her [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadati award for Best Actress]] and [[Awards|Luv lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]].<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-hemmeya-kannadathi-kannada-movie-news-kannada-news-208608</ref><ref>https://www.savasher.com/celebrity-actress/rashmika-mandanna-family-wiki-husband/</ref>\n\nHer next and last release was ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' opposite [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]], which ran for 100-days in a couple of theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitraloka.com/news/17333-chamak-completes-100-days.html|title='CHAMAK' COMPLETES 100 DAYS|work=chitraloka}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/chamak-world-television-premiere-on-saturday/articleshow/64872482.cms|title=Chamak world television premiere on Saturday \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Chamak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/chamak-is-in-safe-zone-kannada_amp-news-204535&ved|title=Chamak is in safe zone-Kannada  Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz}}</ref>\nshe receives critical acclaim from critics for her role as Khushi, ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer Sunayana Suresh stated that \"Rashmika has done a good job at ensuring the audience are with them throughout\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/chamak/amp_movie_review/62294436.cms|title=#Chamak Movie Review {3.5/5}: Critic Review of #Chamak by Times of India|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nWhile ''[[Bangalore Mirror]]''`s writer Shyam Prasad claimed that \"Rashmika sparkles in acting.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/reviews/chamak-movie-review-freshly-old-but-charming-enough/articleshow/62300173.cms|title=Chamak movie review: Freshly old, but charming enough|author=Shyam Prasad|website=Bangalore Mirror|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> ''[[The New Indian Express]]''`s \nSharadhaa wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna emerges as a good artiste in her third outing. The actress, who comes in two shades has taken responsibility for her character, and it shows.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/30/chamak-review-a-fresh-take-on-love-1740026.html|title='Chamak' review: A Fresh Take on Love|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> Latter garnered her first nomination for [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada]] at [[65th Filmfare Awards South]]. three consecutive films in [[Kannada]] language all succeeded at the box office makes her 'hat-trick' heroine in [[Kannada film industry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-mandanna-heroine-of-2017-kannada-news-204253|title=Rashmika Mandanna heroine of 2017 \u2013 Kannada Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz.com}}</ref>\n\n===Debut and fame in Telugu: 2018===\n[[File:Rashmikamandanna.jpg|right|175px|thumb|Rashmika during an inauguration of Mugda Arts Store at [[Hyderabad]] in 2018]]\nShe made her [[Telugu cinema|Telugu film]] debut opposite [[Naga Shourya]] with the film titled ''[[Chalo]]''.,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna \u2019s tollywood debut with Naga Shourya|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/mar/16/rashmika-mandanna-s-tollywood-debut-with-naga-shourya-1581751.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=16 March 2017}}</ref> which ran for 100-days in some theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/chalo-7-days-worldwide-collections-naga-shaurya-starrer-rakes-in-share-of-rs-8-cr/amp_articleshow/62873123.cms|title=Chalo 7 days\u2019 worldwide collections: Naga Shaurya starrer rakes in share of Rs 8 cr  \u2013 Times of India|website=Timesofindia.com}}</ref> critics have been heaped praise on Rashmika for her performance.<ref name=\"Chal\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/> The ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s Hemanth Kumar wrote that \"Rashmika makes a terrific debut and she\u2019s a joy to watch on screen\".<ref name=\"Chal\">{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/chalo-movie-review-naga-shaurya-rashmika-mandanna-stand-out-in-this-quirky-comedy-4333869.html|title=Chalo movie review: Naga Shaurya, Rashmika Mandanna stand out in this quirky comedy- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=3 February 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> While writer of ''[[The Hindu]]''`s Srivathsan Nadadhur stated that she makes a \"Confident debut\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/chalo-review-being-fair-in-love-and-war/article22634327.ece|title='Chalo' review: Being fair in love and war|first=Srivathsan|last=Nadadhur|date=2 February 2018|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''Idlebrain'''s Jeevi   \nnoted that she was \"very cute and acts well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/chalo.html|title=Chalo review by jeevi \u2013 Telugu cinema review \u2013 Naga Shaurya and Rashmika Mandanna|website=Idlebrain.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Greatandra'' stated that \"Kannada heroine Rashmika is cute.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.greatandhra.com/movies/reviews/chalo-review-fun-factor-works-out-87269|title=Chalo, Chalo Rating, Chalo Review, Chalo Telugu Review, Naga Shaurya|first=|last=Venkat|date=2 February 2018|website=greatandhra.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The ''123Telugu'' stated that \"Rashmika makes an impressive debut and suits perfectly in her role.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/chalo-telugu-movie-review.html|title=Chalo Telugu Movie Review|date=3 February 2018|website=123telugu.com}}</ref> ''Telugu360'''s editor wrote that \"Rashmika lent good support to Shaurya with her performance. She is bubbly and effervescent in comedy scenes and shows good promise as an actress.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telugu360.com/chalo-movie-review/|title=Chalo Movie Review, Chalo Review Naga Shourya Chalo movie review|date=2 February 2018|website=Telugu360.com}}</ref>\n\nHer next film was ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to positive reviews and went on to collect over \u20b9130 [[crore]]<ref name=\"Gf\"/> against production budget \u20b95 crore and ran for 100-days in couple of theatres.<ref name=\"Geetha\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-box-office-collection-day-8-vijay-starrer-sets-cash-registers-ringing-bakrid-778539 |title=Geetha Govindam is a small budget movie that is made on a shoe-string budget of \u20b95 crore |work=ibtimes.co.in |access-date=23 August 2018}}</ref> \nand brought her much recognition, making her very popular in [[Telangana]] and [[Andhra Pradesh]], alongside she received immense critical appraisal from both critics and audience, ''[[Hindustan Times]]''`s Priyanka Sundar noted that \"Rashmika have taken this solid plot a notch higher with their delightful performances. Rashmika especially will have you rooting for her throughout the film\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-will-win-you-over-in-this-rom-com/story-yUxgQ8qPoaczB4Bra6IYzO.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda, Rashmika Mandanna will win you over in this rom-com|date=15 August 2018|website=M.hindustantimes.com}}</ref> The writer of ''[[The Times of India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika too sparkles and the scenes between the two is what makes Geetha Govindam so likeable\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/geetha-govindam/movie-review/65411950.cms|title=Geetha Govindam Review {3.5/5}: If you love rom-coms, you're going to lap this up. A big thumbs up!|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref> ''[[The Indian Express]]'' claimed that \"Rashmika as uncompromising Geetha also does a pretty good job\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-5308099/|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda starrer is a charming romantic comedy|date=15 August 2018|website=Indianexpress.com}}</ref> ''[[The Hindu]]'' stated that \"She has an easy screen presence and the potential to handle more well-written parts\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/geetha-govindam-review-this-vijay-deverakonda-film-is-an-antithesis-to-arjun-reddy/article24696712.ece|title='Geetha Govindam' review: The good guy takes over|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|date=15 August 2018|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika and Vijay, who makes it an enjoyable watch. Being paired on-screen for the first time, they  performed their respective roles very well.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakondas-performance-proves-he-is-not-a-one-hit-wonder-4970831.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda's performance proves he is not a one hit wonder- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=15 August 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rashmika mandanna at the Promotions of Devadas.png|right|150px|thumb|Rashmika at promotion of ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'' movie in 2018]]\nHer next release was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'', she shared a space with [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]] and [[Nani (actor)|Nani]] as one of the main lead in the film along [[Akanksha Singh]]. It marked her hat-trick hit film in her career in [[Telugu film industry]] according to few regional reliable sources. She had less screen space, though received critical appraisal for her performance. ''Chitramala''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika Mandanna impressed in her role and made her presence felt.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitramala.in/devadas-telugu-movie-review-276459.html/amp|title=Devadas Telugu Movie Review|date=27 September 2018|website=Chitramala.in}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer states that \"Rashmika deserved better character arc, even though she plays a people of prominence.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/devadas/movieshow/65977659.cms|title=Devadas Movie Review {3.5/5}: The Deva and Das show is thoroughly entertaining|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Continued success and Tamil debut (2019-20) ===\nRashmika started 2019 acting in ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'', Kannada language film opposite [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]], which received decent reviews from the both audience and critics upon the release. And began earning a profit within five-days of its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/yajamana-box-office-collection-darshans-film-profit-zone-just-5-days-end-1st-week-high-note-793347|title=Yajamana box office collection: Darshan's film in profit zone in just 5 days, to end 1st week on high note|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|date=7 March 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Later it collected over \u20b950 crore<ref name=\"Yajj\"/> against production budget \u20b918 crore<ref name=\"Dar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2019/yajamana-day-14-box-office-collection-darshan-continues-to-rule-in-karnataka-slow-run-in-the-us-283815.html|title=Yajamana Day 14 Box Office Collection \u2013 Darshan Continues To Rule In Karnataka But Slow Run In The US \u2013 Filmibeat|date=14 March 2019|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> and ran for over 100-days in some theatres in [[Karnataka]].<ref name=\"Yajj\">{{cite web|url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/entertainment/yajamana-grosses-rs-50-crore-becomes-darshan-s-first-movie-to-cross-the-mark-kgf-rajakumara-the-villain-pod1xd|title=Yajamana grosses Rs 50 crore, becomes Darshan's first movie to cross the mark|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>Darshan's Yajamana hits the 100-day mark - https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/darshans-yajamana-hits-the-100-day-mark/articleshow/69375318.cms</ref>\nShe has been received critical acclaim for her performance as Kaveri, ''[[Times Of India]]'' editor claimed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is cute and her pairing with Darshan works well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/yajamana/movie-review/68213387.cms|title=Yajamana Review {3.5/5}: A must-watch for fans of commercial cinema|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> The ''[[New Indian Express]]'' editor noticed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is allicient as the love interest and justifies the village girl\u2019s character\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2019/mar/02/yajamana-review-this-darshan-starrer-is-a-mass-entertainer-with-social-message-1945439.amp|title='Yajamana' review: This Darshan-starrer is a mass entertainer with social message - The New Indian Express|website=www.newindianexpress.com}}</ref> In 2019, her next film was ''[[Dear Comrade]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to mixed reviews from  both critics and audience. It went on to become a financial failure and touted as first flop at box office in Rashmika's film career. Even though she received overwhelming critical acclaim for her performance in the film as 'Lilly'.<ref>https://www.tollywood.net/article/dear-comrade-to-face-50-loss-in-ceded-huge-disaster/49355/amp</ref> It earned her first [[Award|behindwood's gold medal award]] for best actor critics choice.<ref name=\" BG\">https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/winners-of-7th-behindwoods-gold-medals/rashmika-mandanna-behindwoods-gold-medal-winner-2019.html</ref> She has gone on to win awards honouring her cinematic contributions, including ''Just for Women'''s Magazine \"Sensation of the Year Award\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jfwonline.com/article/the-future-of-cinema-rashmika-mandanna/|title=The future of cinema; Rashmika Mandanna|website=JFW Just for women|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> and the \"Youth Icon\" award in [[Colors Tamil]]'s \"Wonder Women\" Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijays-wife-ajiths-viswasam-director-rashmika-keerthy-suresh-celebs-wonder-women-awards-807492|title=From Vijay's wife to Ajith's Viswasam director, Rashmika Mandanna to Keerthy Suresh, celebs galore at WW Awards|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|date=21 October 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=english|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref> She was invited to participate in a panel discussion (\"Leading Actress\") at the 2019 [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]] (the award function's Golden Jubilee) along with [[Nithya Menen]] moderated by the Indian film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]], which was organized in [[Goa]].<ref>https://www.filmibeat.com/interviews/iffi-2019-kannada-actress-rashmika-mandanna-interview-exclusive-filmibeat-292252.html\n</ref>\n\nIn 2020 Rashmika starred opposite [[Mahesh Babu]] in ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'', which opened to decent reviews from audience and critics upon the release and went on to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing films]] in the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industry,<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-9-day-box-office-collection-anil-ravipudi-scores-career-best-mahesh-babu-811970</ref> and emerged as Rashmika's career highest profit erner to date by collecting \u20b92 billion in just 10-days.<ref name=\"SLN\">https://www.businesstoday.in/trending/box-office/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-film-ahead-of-mahesh-babu-sarileru-neekevvaru/story/394286.html</ref><ref name=\"SLN 1st week collection\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/sankranti-telugu-releases-ala-vaikuntapuramloo-sarileru-neekevvaru-strike-gold-at-the-box-office/story-Bm8033vi57uLu8fTVHkqJK.html|title=Sankranti Telugu releases Ala Vaikuntapuramloo, Sarileru Neekevvaru strike gold at the box office|website=Hindustan Times|date=20 January 2020|access-date=21 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 3 Days\">{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/mahesh-babu-film-sarileru-neekevvaru-earns-rs-103-crore-6216179/|title=Mahesh Babu film Sarileru Neekevvaru earns Rs 103 crore|website=Indian Express|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-collection-mahesh-babu-and-rashmika-mandanna-starrer-hits-the-100-crore-mark-in-three-days/articleshow/73247929.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Box-Office Collection: Mahesh Babu and Rashmika Mandanna starrer hits the 100-crore mark in three days|website=The Times of India|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> And went on to collect over \u20b92.6 billion in 50-days theatrical run at worldwide box office.<ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection The Statesman\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/southern_cinema/sarileru-neekevvaru-mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-box-office-1502861238.html|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru: Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days at box office. It has grossed Rs 260 crore till now|website=[[The Statesman (India)|The Statesman]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection India TV\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/regional-cinema/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-593698|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of Sarileru Neekevvaru at box office|website=[[India TV]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection Outlook India\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-of-sarileru-neekevvaru-at-box-office/1747919|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of ''Sarileru Neekevvaru'' at box office|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> The reviewer of ''[[Times Of India]]'' Neeshita Nyayapati, stated \"Rashmika Mandanna woos, gets hyper, dances, has a catch-line, all for the male lead, but why she exists in this tale, other than to fawn over him is a mystery.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru/movie-review/73198148.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=The Times of India|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> The editor of ''[[India Today]]'' Janani K, claimed that \"We see Rashmika playing a typical 'loosu ponnu' (read: A mindless heroine who acts like a kid) who keeps stalking Mahesh Babu.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-mahesh-babu-film-is-utterly-disappointing-1635966-2020-01-11|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=India Today|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> Whereas, the editor of ''[[Hans India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna has impressed with her performance.\"<ref>https://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527\nhttps://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527</ref> Her next Telugu film in 2020 was ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' opposite [[Nithiin]], which opened to positive response from the both critics and audience.<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-813649\n</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/bheeshma-box-office-nithiins-highest-opening-in-the-telugu-states/articleshow/74253897.cms</ref> The film went on to become a financial hit at worldwide box office by collecting over \u20b950 crore.<ref>https://telugu.news18.com/news/movies/nithiin-bheeshma-movie-collects-50-crore-gross-world-wide-for-first-week-sr-464782.html</ref><ref>https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/nithiin-and-rashmika-starrer-bheeshma-movie-collects-rs-50-crores-gross-world-wind/articleshow/74391410.cms</ref> She received praise for her performance as Chaitra. The ''[[Firstpost]]'''s editor Hemanth Kumar praised her chemistry with Nithiin.<ref>https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bheeshma-movie-review-nithiin-rashmika-mandannas-romantic-drama-is-a-breezy-entertainer-8070741.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!Year!! Films !! Roles !! Director(s) !! Languages \n!Notes\n|-\n|2016\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| Saanvi Joseph\n| [[Rishab Shetty]]\n|rowspan='3'|[[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n|Kannada Debut and first film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| Kushi\n| [[Suni (director)|Suni]]\n|Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Kannada]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chalo]]''\n| L. Karthika\n| Venky Kudumula\n| rowspan='3'|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Telugu Debut\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]\n|Won \u2013 [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress (Critics) - Telugu]]<br />Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''\n| Inspector Pooja\n| Sriram Aditya\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n!scope=\"row\" |''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]''\n| Kaveri\n|[[Pon Kumaran]] <br> [[V. Harikrishna]]\n|[[Kannada]]\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  |''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n| Lilly\n| [[Bharat Kamma]]\n|rowspan='3'|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2020\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]''\n|Samskruthi\n|[[Anil Ravipudi]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]''\n|Chaitra\n|Venky Kudumula\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/bheeshma-nithiin-rashmika-mandanna-wraps-up-the-first-schedule-of-their-upcoming-film/articleshow/70429744.cms|title=Bheeshma: Nithiin, Rashmika Mandanna wraps up the first schedule of their upcoming film - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/bheeshma-to-arrive-on-feb-21-603864|title='Bheeshma' to arrive on Feb 21|last=India|first=The Hans|date=9 February 2020|website=www.thehansindia.com|language=en|access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#ffc;\"|''[[Pogaru]]'' {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|[[Nanda Kishore]]\n|[[Kannada]]\n|Filming<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/05/rashmika-mandanna-checks-into-dhruva-sarja-starrer-pogaru-1894325.html|title=Rashmika Mandanna checks into Dhruva Sarja-starrer 'Pogaru'|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref> (Dubbing Stage)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/nov/28/dhruva-sarja-to-resume-work-for-pogaru-15751.html|title=Dhruva Sarja to resume work for Pogaru|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[Sultan (2020 film)|Sultan]]'' {{dagger}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|Bakkiyaraj Kannan\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n|Post-production, Tamil Debut<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/karthis-sultan-to-hit-screens-during-summer-holidays/articleshow/73297255.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sultan-rashmika-mandanna-confirms-the-title-of-her-next-film-with-karthi-1581520-2019-08-16|title=Sultan: Rashmika Mandanna confirms the title of her next film with Karthi|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019|agency=Ist}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[Pushpa (film)|Pushpa]] ''{{dagger}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|[[Sukumar (director)|Sukumar]]\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Filming\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Language\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| [[South Indian International Movie Awards|South Indian International Movie Awards for Best Debut Actress (Leading Role)]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" | [[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Utsavam|IIFA Utsavam Award for Best Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2018\n| [[Awards|Luv Lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadathi Award for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Awards South for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|South Indian International Movie Awards for Bes]]\n[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|t Actress in Leading Role]]\n|-\n|[[Awards|TSR TV9 National Award for Best Actress]] \n|{{Nominated}} \n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n|[[Filmibeat|Filmibeat Award for Best Debutant Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|''[[Chalo]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards|Zee Cine Awards for Favorite Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Sri Kala Sudha Telugu Awards for Best Debut Heroine]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award for Best Actress]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Award|JFW award - Sensational Actor]]\n|{{Won}}<ref>VBJ JFW Awards 2019: Yet Another Unforgettable Success! https://jfwonline.com/article/vbj-jfw-awards-2019-yet-another-unforgettable-success/</ref>\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Awards South Best Actress Critics Choice]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Behindwoods Gold Medal (Best Actor Critics Choice)]]\n|''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n|{{Won}}<ref name=\"BG\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Rashmika Mandanna}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=8612305|title=Rashmika Mandanna}}\n\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Female D\u00e9butante}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Kodava people]]\n[[Category:People from Kodagu district]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n", "name_user": "106.217.115.72", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rashmika_Mandanna"}
{"title_page": "Kanyakumari district", "text_new": "Rowdy place in kanyakumari district           \n\n'''Annai nagar''' \n\n'''Kanyakumari district''' is the southernmost district in [[Tamil Nadu]] state and mainland [[India]]. It stands second in terms of population density among the districts of [[Tamil Nadu]] and the second most [[Urbanization|urbanized]], next only to [[Chennai district]].<ref>[http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kumari-second-most-urbanised-tn-district/168794-60-118.html Kumari second most urbanised TN district - South India - [[Tamil Nadu]] - ibnlive<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It is also the richest district in [[Tamil Nadu]] in terms of per capita income,<ref>http://www.tn.gov.in/dear/State%20Income.pdf</ref> and also tops the state in Human Development Index (HDI), literacy and education.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/kanniyakumari-tops-hdi-rankings/article18470625.ece</ref><ref>http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/tns-literacy-rate-at-new-high/article3146578.ece</ref> The district's headquarters is [[Nagercoil]].\n\nKanyakumari district has a varied topography with sea on three sides and the mountains of the [[Western Ghats]] bordering the northern side. Except for a small stretch of land to the west of [[Kanyakumari]] town, almost the entire district is sandwiched between the [[Western Ghats]] and the [[Arabian Sea]] - the only district in [[Tamilnadu]] state facing the [[Arabian Sea]].\n\nGeologically, the landmass of the district is much younger when compared to the rest of the state - faulted as late as 2.5 million years during the [[Miocene]], after which numerous [[Marine transgression|transgression]], as well as regression of sea, had shaped the western coast of the district.\n\nHistorically, [[Nanjinad]] and [[Edai Nadu]] which comprise the present day Kanyakumari district, was ruled by various Tamil and Malayalam dynasties: the [[Venad|Venad Kingdom]], [[Pandyan dynasty|Pandyans]], the [[Chera dynasty|Cheras]], the [[Chola dynasty|Cholas]], the [[Ay kingdom|Ays]] and the [[Nayak dynasty|Nayaks]]. A few artifacts unearthed by archeological excavations in there. It was part of the princely state of [[Travancore]] during the colonial times prior to [[Independence Day (India)|India's independence]]; four of the eight [[tehsil]]s of [[Thiruvananthapuram district]] were separated from erstwhile Travancore Kingdom to form the new district of Kanyakumari, and they were made the part of [[Madras Presidency]] under recommendations from the [[States Reorganisation Commission]] in 1956. The Presidency was later renamed Tamil Nadu and Kanyakumari, today, is one of the 37 districts of [[Tamil Nadu]] state.\n\nMany historical assumptions persist in the district and state, which associate sages such as [[Vyasa]], [[Agastya]], [[Tolk\u0101ppiyam|Tolkappiyar]], [[Avvaiyar]] and [[Thiruvalluvar]] to the district. The district is also the birthplace of [[Ayyavazhi]].\n\n==History==\n{{see also|Ay kingdom|Venad|Sangam period|Travancore|Chera dynasty}}\n{{see also|Merger of Kanyakumari with Madras State}}\n\nThe area that comprises the current Kanyakumari district was a part of the old Ay kingdom of the first and second Sangham ages. Following the decline of the Ay kingdoms, the area became Venad, with its capital [[Padmanabhapuram]] located North, North West of Nagercoil. The wealth of the Nanjilnadu beckoned many invaded kings including the Nayaks and later an Islamist army during the reign of [[Umayamma Rani]]. The [[Venad]] region was in anarchy before [[Marthanda Varma]] ascended the throne in 1729 AD. Under their rule anarchy was dominant in [[Kanyakumari]] region. However, [[Marthanda Varma]] brought a sense of disorder under control by annexing the nearby territories, putting down the feudal lords and establishing the strong state of [[Travancore]]. He had also bought some portions of Kanyakumari from the then viceroy making it the southern boundary. Under his rule, the district improved in a social context as well as economically. The famous [[battle of Colachel]] took place in the district. Later, the Maharajas of Travancore built the forts at Aramboly ( Aralvaimozhy) to prevent any invasion from the Carnatic Kings. Key elements of [[Velu Thampi Dalawa|Velu Thampi Dalawa's]] revolt occurred in the area and the English East India company's army under Col. Leger broke through the fortifications and entered Travancore in 1810. In the year 1949, the area became a part of the reestablished [[Travancore]] Cochin state. The people of Agasteeswarem, Thovalai, Kalkulam and Vilavancode taluks, which formed the southern divisions of the former district of [[Trivandrum]], were predominantly Tamil speaking people. An extreme agitation by Tamil speaking residents under the leadership of [[A. Nesamony|Marshal Nesamony]] took place for including Kanyakumari within [[Tamil Nadu]]. Eventually the merger happened in 1956 based on [[States Reorganisation Act, 1956|language reorganization of states]].\n\nHistorically, [[Nanjilnadu]] (Agastheeswaram and Thovalai taluks) and [[Eda Nadu]] (Vilavancode and Kalkulam taluks) which comprises the present Kanyakumari district. The district were ruled by various dynasties: [[Venad|Venad Kingdom]], [[Travancore|Travancore Kingdom]], the [[Chera dynasty|Cheras]], the [[Chola dynasty|Cholas]], the [[Ay kingdom|Ays]] and the [[Nayak dynasty|Nayaks]]. A few artifacts were unearthed by archeological excavations in parts of the district. The district was part of the princely state of [[Travancore]] during the colonial times prior to [[Independence Day (India)|India's independence]]; four of the eight [[tehsil]]s of [[Thiruvananthapuram district]] were separated to form the new district of Kanyakumari in 1956 following the demands of reunion made by the Tamil speaking majority people (about 70% of the population), who feels that their feelings were suppressed by the erstwhile Travancore Kingdom which has Malayalam majority population. The four taluks were made the part of then [[Madras Presidency]] under recommendations from the [[States Reorganisation Commission]] in 1956. The Presidency was later renamed Tamil Nadu in 1969 and Kanyakumari, today, is one of the 37 districts of [[Tamil Nadu]] state.\n\nThe district is the birthplace of [[Ayyavazhi]], the [[Henotheism|henotheistic]] belief initiated by [[Hari Gopalan Citar|Hari Gopalan Seedar]], one among the 5 prime disciples of [[Ayya Vaikundar]]. The social, religious and cultural history of the 19th century Kanyakumari district is intrinsically inter-twined with those of Ayyavazhi. Many historical assumptions persist in the district and state, which associate with sages namely [[Vyasa]], [[Agastya]], [[Tolk\u0101ppiyam|Tolkappiyar]], [[Avvaiyar]] and [[Thiruvalluvar]].\n\n== Geography ==\n=== Location ===\nThe district is situated between 77\u00b015' and 77\u00b036' east longitude and 8\u00b003' and 8\u00b035' north latitude. The district has borders with [[Tirunelveli district]] in the North & North East, the [[Gulf of Mannar]] in the East, the [[Indian Ocean]] in the South, the [[Arabian Sea]] in the West and the [[Thiruvananthapuram District]] ([[Kerala]]) in the West.\n\nKanyakumari District is divided into two regions: Edai nadu and Nanjil nadu. Vilavancode and Kalkulam taluks are in the Edai nadu region which consists of full stretched Western ghats. Thovalai and Agastheeswaram taluks are present in the Nanjil nadu region. Aralvaimozhy pass separates these two regions. Also the boundary of these regions is Vaezhimalai ( Vaezhi Hills).\n\nKanyakumari district has a varied topography with sea on three sides and the mountains of the [[Western Ghats]] bordering the northern side. Geologically, the landmass of the district is much younger when compared to the rest of state - faulted as late as 2.5 million years during the [[Miocene]], after which numerous [[Marine transgression|transgression]], as well as regression of sea, had shaped the western coast of the district.\n\n==Places of interest==\n\n''' Thirparappu Waterfalls '''\n\nThirparappu Waterfalls is the famous waterfalls in Kanyakumari District. It is also known as 'Courtallam of Kanyakumari'. Almost all the days water falls here. So tourists will always be interested to come here. There is a swimming pool near the waterfalls. At the upper side of the waterfalls, one can ride on boat. There is a children's park near the waterfalls. Famous Mahadevar Temple is very near to the waterfalls. The waterfalls is {{cvt|7|km}} from [[Kulasekaram]].,Actually the waterfalls is exactly 34 km from city centre,Nagercoil.\n\n''' Manimedai '''\n\nManimedai is the situated in the central part of [[Nagercoil]]. Manimedai literally means High Clock. It's the symbol of the Nagercoil Town. A clock is placed in a High Clock gauge, so the place becomes Manimedai. The construction of Clock gauge begins in 1892 in the period of [[Travancore]] Maharajas. After construction, it was opened by His Highness Sree Moolam Thirunal Varma, The king of Travancore. The clock placed in the gauge was gifted to the English missionary in Nagercoil. Maharaja got it and placed it in the gauge.\n\n''' Mathur Aqueduct '''\n\nThe aqueduct was built to pass the cultivable water between two mountains. Mathur Aqueduct was built between Aruvikkarai and Mudhalaaru in Paraliyaru River. The aqueduct was built by Former Chief Minister of TamilNadu Perunthalaivar Thiru Kamarajar. Mathur aqueduct was South Asia's largest aqueduct. The aqueduct is {{cvt|1240|ft}} long, {{cvt|101|ft}} high with 28 giant pillars. It is {{cvt|3|km}} from [[Thiruvattar]] and 26 km from Nagercoil.\n\n''' Padmanabhapuram palace '''\n\nBefore centuries, the houses that has all the facilities are known as Palaces. The rulers of states, the Kings resides in such Palaces. [[Padmanabhapuram palace]] was once the official residence of Travancore Kings. [[Padmanabhapuram palace]] was built in [[Kerala]] styled Architecture with woods. The palace was built in 18th century by Travancore King Thiru [[Marthanda Varma|Anizham Thirunal Marthanda Varma]]. The palace was situated in 6 1/2 acres in 186 acres fort. Here one can enjoy seeing things used by Travancore Kings. The palace was under the control of Kerala Government. The palace is situated just 2&nbsp;km from [[Thuckalay]].\n\n''' Udayagiri Fort '''\n\nUdayagiri Fort was situated just 10&nbsp;km from [[Parvathipuram, Tamil Nadu|Parvathipuram]]. The fort was situated in 22\u00bd hectares in a place called Puliyoorkurichi. The fort was used by the erstwhile Travancore Kings as the production unit of Explosives and as Practising Unit for war. The Fort was maintained by the Ministry of Forests, Government of Tamilnadu. In the fort, one can see [[deer]], [[Peacock]], [[monkeys]] etc.\n\n''' Vattakkottai '''\n\nThe word 'Vattakkottai' means Circle Fort. The Fort is circle in shape and the name came thus. The Fort was constructed along the seashore in East coast. The fort was situated in 3 1/2 acres with compound stones constructed for 25 metres height. The fort was constructed by Travancore Army Chief Dilanai. The fort was built to restrict the invasion by other rulers and also to store war equipments. The fort was under the control of Archaeological Department, Government of India. It is situated just 6;km north from [[Kanyakumari]] and just 2 km south from [[Anjugramam]].\n\n\n'''Vivekananda Rock''' \n\n[[Vivekananda Rock Memorial]] is a popular tourist monument in Vavathurai in Kanyakumari District. It is located just 500 Meters east in main land of [[Vavathurai]]. The rock was built in 1970 in honour of [[Swami Vivekananda]] who is said to have attained enlightenment on the rock. Vivekanand was a disciple of Swami [[Ramakrishna Paramahansa]] . According to local legends, [[Devi Kanya Kumari |Goddess Kumari]]  performed Tapas in devotion of [[lord Shiva]] in these rocks. The rocks are surrounded by the [[Laccadive Sea]].\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nFor administrative purposes, the district comprises six taluks: [[Thovalai]], [[Agastheeswaram]], [[Kalkulam]], [[Killiyur, Kanniyakumari|Killiyur]], [[Thiruvattar]] and [[Vilavancode]]. It has nine blocks &mdash; [[Agastheeswaram]], [[Rajakkamangalam]], [[Thovalai]], [[Kurunthancode]], [[Thuckalay]], [[Thiruvattar]], [[Killiyur, Kanniyakumari|Killiyur]], [[Munchirai]] and [[Melpuram]]. There is a municipal corporation in the district which is Nagercoil. There are also three municipalities, they are [[Padmanabhapuram]], [[Colachel]] and [[Kuzhithurai]].\n\nAt the lower levels of administration, there are 95 village [[panchayat]]s and a further 55 special category village panchayats.\n\nThe major towns of the district include:\n* Agastheeswaram taluk: [[Nagercoil]], [[Kanyakumari]], [[Anjugramam]], [[Agastheeswaram]], [[Suchindram]] and [[Rajakkamangalam]].\n* Thovalai taluk: [[Boothapandi]], [[Thovalai]], [[Azhagiapandiapuram]] and [[Aralvaimozhy]].\n* Kalkulam taluk: [[Padmanabhapuram]], [[Thuckalay]], [[Colachel]], [[Kalkulam]], [[Thiruvithamcode]], [[Eraniel]], [[Kurunthancode]], and [[Thingalnagar]].\n* Thiruvattar taluk: [[Thiruvattar]], and [[Kulasekaram]].\n* Killiyur Taluk: [[Killiyur, Kanniyakumari|Killiyur]], and [[Karungal]].\n* Vilavancode Taluk: [[Kuzhithurai]], [[Marthandam]], [[Vilavancode]], [[Kaliyakkavilai]], [[Munchirai]], [[Kollemcode]], [[Manjalumoodu]], [[Arumanai]], and [[Melpuram]].\n\n==Medical services==\nThe district has Government Medical College & Hospital at [[Acharipallam]]. Government Head hospital is at [[Thuckalay]], which is known as Padmanabhapuram Government hospital. Other Government hospitals are at [[Colachel]], [[Kulasekaram]], [[Arumanai]], [[Karungal]], [[Boothapandi]], and [[Kanyakumari]]. The Government Primary Health centres are at [[Kottaram]], [[Agastheeswaram]], [[Alagappapuram]], [[Aralvaimozhy]], [[Arumanallur]], Chenbagaramanputhoor, [[Ganapathipuram]], [[Marungoor]], [[Rajakkamangalam]], [[Muttom, Kanyakumari|Muttom]], [[Thovalai]], Vellichanthai, [[Kurunthancode]], Arudesam, Thadikkarankonam, [[Edaikodu]], Kannanoor, Keelkulam, [[Killiyur, Kanniyakumari|Killiyur]], [[Kollemcode]], Kothanallur, [[Melpuram]], [[Munchirai]], Naduvoorkarai, [[Thirunattalam]], Olavilai, [[Palliyadi]], Pathukani, Pechiparai, Singalayerpuri, Surulodu, [[Thengapattanam]], Kuttakuzhi, [[Thiruvattar]], [[Thiruvithamcode]] and [[Thoothoor]].\n\n==Language==\nTamil is the most widely spoken language in the district, though there are significant numbers of native Malayalam speakers (Approximately 30% of the population). Tamil in Kanyakumari is the mixture of Tamil and Malayalam, especially in the western part of the district. English can be understood by two-thirds of the district's population.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n==Demography==\n{{historical populations|11=1901|12=3,59,248|13=1911|14=4,22,260|15=1921|16=4,94,125|17=1931|18=5,81,851|19=1941|20=6,76,975|21=1951|22=8,26,380|23=1961|24=9,96,915|25=1971|26=12,22,549|27=1981|28=14,23,399|29=1991|30=16,00,349|31=2001|32=16,76,034|33=2011|34=18,70,374|percentages=pagr|footnote=source:<ref>[http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/A2_Data_Table.html Decadal Variation In Population Since 1901]</ref>|align=right}}According to [[2011 census of India|2011 census]], Kanniyakumari district had a population of 1,870,374 with a sex-ratio of 1,019 females for every 1,000 males, much above the national average of 929.<ref name=\"dashboard\">{{cite web|title=Census Info 2011 Final population totals|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/censusinfodashboard/index.html|publisher=Office of The Registrar General and Census Commissioner, Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India|year=2013|accessdate=26 January 2014}}</ref> A total of 182,350 were under the age of six, constituting 92,835 males and 89,515 females. [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes]] accounted for 3.97% and .39% of the population respectively. The district had a total of 483,539 households. There were a total of 679,620 workers, comprising 12,229 cultivators, 51,350 main agricultural labourers, 21,078 in house hold industries, 468,001 other workers, 126,962 marginal workers, 3,381 marginal cultivators, 21,517 marginal agricultural labourers, 14,711 marginal workers in household industries and 87,353 other marginal workers.<ref name=2011census>{{cite web|title=Census Info 2011 Final population totals - Kanniyakumari district|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=701252|publisher=Office of The Registrar General and Census Commissioner, Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India|year=2013|accessdate=26 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nAverage literacy rate of Kanyakumari in 2011 were 91.75 compared to 87.55 of 2001. If things are looked out at gender wise, male and female literacy were 93.65 and 89.90 respectively. For 2001 census, same figures stood at 90.37 and 84.79 in Kanyakumari District. Total literate in Kanyakumari District were 1,548,738 of which male and female were 780,541 and 768,197 respectively. In 2001, Kanyakumari District had 1,308,322 in its district.\n\n===Urban population===\nOut of the total Kanyakumari population for 2011 census, 82.33 percent lives in urban regions of district. In total 1,539,802 people lives in urban areas of which males are 761,407 and females are 778,395. Sex ratio in urban region of Kanyakumari district is 1022 as per 2011 census data. Similarly child sex ratio in Kanyakumari district was 966 in 2011 census. Child population (0-6) in urban region was 148,570 of which males and females were 75,573 and 72,997. This child population figure of Kanyakumari district is 9.93% of total urban population. Average literacy rate in Kanyakumari district as per census 2011 is 91.96% of which males and females are 93.92% and 90.06% literates respectively. In actual number 1,279,358 people are literate in urban region of which males and females are 644,109 and 635,249 respectively.\n\n===Rural population===\nAs per 2011 census, 17.67% population of Kanyakumari districts lives in rural areas of villages. The total Kanyakumari district population living in rural areas is 330,572 of which males and females are 164,938 and 165,634 respectively. In rural areas of Kanyakumari district, sex ratio is 1004 females per 1000 males. If child sex ratio data of Kanyakumari district is considered, figure is 957 girls per 1000 boys. Child population in the age 0-6 is 33,780 in rural areas of which males were 17,262 and females were 16,518. The child population comprises 10.47% of total rural population of Kanyakumari district. Literacy rate in rural areas of Kanyakumari district is 90.76% as per census data 2011. Gender wise, male and female literacy stood at 92.39 and 89.16 percent respectively. In total, 269,380 people were literate of which males and females were 136,432 and 132,948 respectively.\n\n==Religion==\nDuring 2011, total population of the district is 1,870,374, among them 909,872 (48.65%) are Hindus, 876,299 (46.85%) are Christians, 78,590 (4.2%) are Muslims, 438 (0.02%) are Buddhists, 160 (0.01%) are Sikhs, 156 (0.01%) are Jains, 10 (0.001%) are Others and 4,849 (0.26%) are \"not stated\".<ref>http://www.census2011.co.in/census/district/51-kanniyakumari.html</ref>\n\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kanyakumari District (2011)<ref name=\"census2011\">{{cite web |title=Population by religion community \u2013 2011 |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/C-01/DDW00C-01%20MDDS.XLS |website=Census of India, 2011 |publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150825155850/http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/C-01/DDW00C-01%20MDDS.XLS |archivedate=25 August 2015}}</ref>\n|label1 = [[Hinduism]]\n|color1 = orange\n|value1 = 48.6\n|label2 = [[Christianity]]\n|color2 = DodgerBlue\n|value2 = 46.9\n|label3 = [[Islam]]\n|color3 = Green\n|value3 = 4.2\n|label4 = Other\n|color4 = Yellow\n|value4 = 0.3\n}}\n\n==Festivals==\n[[File:Thiru Nizhal Thangal of Attoor.jpg|thumb|right|An octo-circular [[Ayyavazhi]] [[Nizhal Thangal of Attoor|Nizhal Thangal]] near [[Thiruvattar]] on the [[Martandam]]-[[Kulasekaram]] road.]]\nThe [[Mandaikadu]] festival is celebrated in March by people of the district and by those in Kerala. Traditionally, participants would chant while walking and other people would provide them with butter, milk, water, [[jaggery]], and coffee. The festival, which is celebrated for ten days, later became a social function, especially on Sunday.\n\nThe [[Ayya vaikunda Avataram]], is widely celebrated throughout the district.<ref>[[Dina Thanthi|The Daily Thanthi]], ''Nagercoil Edition'', 5/4/2006.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dinamalar.com/2006mar03/general_tn3.asp |title=Dina Malar |accessdate=2007-02-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927021910/http://www.dinamalar.com/2006mar03/general_tn3.asp |archivedate=27 September 2007 }}</ref> The [[Kodiyettru Thirunal]] is celebrated in the religious headquarters of [[Swamithope pathi]] and attracts large crowds<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/06/03/stories/2008060351640300.htm |work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=2008-06-03 |title=''\"Thousands of people witnessed the Vaikasi car festival at Vaikundar temple at Swamithoppu...\"''}}</ref> from Tamil Nadu and across India.<ref>[[Dina Thanthi|The Daily Thanthi]] ([[Nagercoil]] Edition), 29-1-2007, Page 12, \"Devotees from the districts of Kanyakumari, [[Tirunelveli]], [[Thoothukkudi]], [[Theni]], [[Chennai]], [[Coimbatore]] and also from the State of [[Kerala]] participated in the Car festival.\"</ref><ref>[[Dina Thanthi|The Daily Thanthi]] ([[Coimbatore]] Edition), 3-6-2008, Page 4, \"Thousands of devotees from the districts of [[Madurai]], [[Tirunelveli]], [[Thoothukkudi]], [[Theni]], [[Coimbatore]] and also from the State of [[Kerala]] participated in the Car festival.\"</ref><ref>[[Dinakaran]] ([[Tirunelveli]] Edition), 3-6-2008, Page 6, \"Thousands of devotees from the districts of Kanyakumari, [[Tirunelveli]], [[Thoothukkudi]], [[Virudhunager]], [[Theni]], and also from the State of [[Kerala]] participated in the Car festival.\"</ref> Onam is also celebrated in many places throughout Kanyakumari district, especially in the western part of the district.\n\n[[Christianity]] plays a vital role in the district's religious map. The district's engagement with [[Christianity]] dates back to 1st century A.D. Traditional followers are seen even now in the coastal belt of the district. [[St. Francis Xavier]] made his religious preachings in and around [[Kottar]]. Kottar St. Xavier Cathedral is the first church named after him in whole world. The church was dedicated to him even before he was conferred the Sainthood. Every year December 3 is celebrated as St. Xavier's day. The church is also the cathedral church of Kottar diocese.\n\n==Transport and highways==\n''' Roadways '''\n\nThere are two major [[National Highway (India)|National Highways]] (NH) roads originating from Kanyakumari town. One is the National Highway 44 which connects Kanyakumari with Srinagar of [[Jammu & Kashmir]]. NH 44 connects North India with South India. The road passes through [[Madurai]], [[Bengaluru]], [[Hyderabad]], [[Nagpur]], [[Jhansi]], [[Delhi]] and [[Jalandhar]]. It covers 3745 kilometres. The other is the National Highway 66 that connects Kanyakumari with [[Panvel]] (38&nbsp;km from [[Mumbai]]) in Maharashtra. NH 66 roughly runs North-South parallel to the western ghats. It passes through [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kochi]], [[Kozhikode]], [[Mangaluru]], [[Udupi]], [[Margoa]] and [[Ratnagiri]]. Nagercoil, the district capital is well connected with the rest of [[Tamil Nadu]].\n\nThe Government transport body \" State Express Transport Corporation \" ( S.E.T.C ) is operating direct buses to [[Chennai]], [[Ootacamund]], [[Coimbatore]], [[Vellore]], [[Chidambaram]], [[Thiruchirappalli]], [[Kodaikanal]], [[Tirupur]], [[Erode]], [[Kalpakkam]], [[Velankanni]], and [[Thiruvannamalai]]. It also operates direct buses to [[Bengaluru]], [[Pondicherry]] and [[Tirupati]]. Some bus services to the aforesaid destinations are originating from [[Kanyakumari]], [[Colachel]], [[Marthandam]], [[Kulasekaram]], [[Kaliyakkavilai]], and [[Thiruvananthapuram]].\n\nAn another Government Transport body \" Tamilnadu State Road Transport Corporation \" (T.N.S.T.C) operates direct buses to various destinations inside [[Tamil Nadu]]. Some of the terminating stations are [[Chennai]], [[Tiruppur]], [[Periyakulam]], [[Kodaikanal]], [[Rameswaram]], [[Thiruchirappalli]], [[Dindigul]], [[Thanjavur]], [[Palani]], [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]], [[Coimbatore]], [[Karaikudi]], [[Kumily]], [[Bodinayakkanur]], [[Erode]], and [[Sivakasi]]. Most of these buses starts their journey from [[Nagercoil]] while some buses starts from [[Kanyakumari]], [[Marthandam]], [[Colachel]], [[Kulasekaram]], and [[Kaliyakkavilai]]. TNSTC also operates frequent bus services to [[Madurai]], [[Tirunelveli]], [[Tiruchendur]], [[Tuticorin]], and [[Thiruvananthapuram]].\n\n'''Railways'''\n\nThere is a railway station located at Kanyakumari where many trains starts and ends their journey. The [[Vivek Express]] starting from Kanyakumari is the longest running train in India. It connects Kanyakumari with [[Dibrugarh]], in [[Assam]]. [[Nagercoil Junction railway station]] is the primary railway station of the district which is located near Kottar and also commonly known as Kottar Railway station. Kottar is well connected by State Transport buses. There is also an another railway station in Nagercoil. It is known as Nagercoil Town railway station. Ministry of Railways is developing the station in high pitch.  Rail station and its surroundings are developing in a high manner. There is good rail connectivity from Nagercoil, the district capital to most parts of the country with daily trains running to [[Mumbai]], [[Chennai]], [[Bengaluru]], [[Guruvayur]], [[Coimbatore]], [[Trichy]], [[Mangaluru]] , [[Tambaram]] etc. and weekly trains to [[New Delhi]], [[Kolkata]], [[Gujarat]], [[Hyderabad]], [[Pondicherry]], [[Bilaspur, Chhattisgarh|Bilaspur]], [[Rameswaram]], [[North East India]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]], etc. The other stations in the district are Eraniel, Palliyadi, Kuzhithurai, and Kuzhithurai west. Passenger trains connect [[Nagercoil]] with [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kollam]], [[Punalur]], [[Kottayam]], [[Tirunelveli]], [[Madurai]], and [[Coimbatore]].\n\n'''Airways'''\n\nThe nearest International airport is [[Trivandrum International Airport]] which is 76&nbsp;km from Kanyakumari. The Civil Aviation Ministry is planning to construct an airport near Swamithoppu in Kanyakumari District as the initiative attracts many international tourists to the district.\n\n==Education==\nThe district is popular for its educational excellence. Schools and Colleges of higher education are found throughout the district. Government schools are in good numbers comparing private institutions. Government schools compete with private schools in excellence.\n \nThe district is home to many age old educational institutions.Amrita Vidyalayam Kanyakumari,Leading Cbse school in the district,Sethu Lakshmi Bai (S.L.B) Higher secondary school which is situated in Nagercoil is the important and popular school in the district. Other important schools in Nagercoil are D.V.D Higher secondary school, Kavimani Desiya Vinayagam Pillai (K.D.V.P) Higher secondary school for Girls, St. Joseph Convent for Girls, Duthie Higher secondary school for Girls, Carmel Higher secondary school for Boys, and Little flower Higher secondary school for Girls. Other reputed institutions in the district are Amala Convent ( Thuckalay ),V. K. P Higher Secondary School(Colachel), L.M.S Higher secondary school for Boys and Girls ( Marthandam),Bapuji Memorial Higher Secondary school( Manavalakirichy), Alphonsa matriculation (beach road)\n\nThe district constitutes tens of colleges, mainly arts, science and engineering colleges. The [[Scott Christian College]], founded by [[William Tobias Ringeltaube]] in Nagercoil, is more than 120 years old and is one of the earliest colleges in India and the oldest college in the Madras Presidency. The [[South Travancore Hindu College]] is also an old college in Nagercoil established in 1952. Other main colleges in Nagercoil are [[Pioneer Kumaraswamy college]], Women's Christian College, and Holy Cross College. Other important colleges in the district are Sree Ayyappa College for Women ( Chunkankadai ), Sivanthi Aditanar College ( Pillayarpuram ), Arignar Anna College ( Aralvaimozhy ), Lekshmipuram College of Arts and Science (Lekshmipuram), Muslim Arts College ( Thiruvithamcode ), [[Rohini College of Engineering & Technology]], [[Anjugramam]] and Nesamony Memorial Christian College ( Marthandam ). Government Polytechnic college and Government Engineering College are situated in Konam, 5&nbsp;km from Nagercoil.  Kanniyakumari Government Medical College was established at Asaripallam, Nagercoil in 2001. Government Colleges for Arts and Science were built in Kanyakumari and Nagercoil.\nThere are some colleges which are built especially for women like Arunachala college of engineering (Manavilai ),Vins Christian College for women (chunkankadai).\n\n==Rivers==\n\n[[File:View from Mathur Bridge.JPG|thumb|View from the [[Mathur Hanging Trough]] bridge with the [[Pahrali]] river flowing below.]]\nThe major river in the district is [[Thamirabarani River|Thamirabarani]] locally known as Kuzhithurai Aaru (Kuzhithurai River). This river has two major tributaries, Kodhayaru and Paraliyaru, with the [[Pechiparai Dam]] and [[Perunchani Dam]], respectively, built across them. There are many tributaries for the Kodayar River of which [[Chittar River|Chittar]] I and Chittar II, with their dams, are the major ones. The origin of Tambaraparani River is in the [[Western Ghats]] and the river confluences with [[Laccadive Sea]] near Thengapattanam, about {{convert|56|km|mi}} west of Kanyakumari town.\n\n==Forests==\n[[File:Pechiparai Reservoir, Kanyakumari District - with Western Ghats in the background.jpg|thumb|The [[Western Ghats]] at Pechiparai, Kanyakumari District]]\nThe forests in Kanyakumari District are about 75 million years old. Of the total district area of 1671.3&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, government forests occupy an area of 504.86&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> which comes to about 30.2 percent of the geographical area of the district.<ref>[http://www.forests.tn.nic.in/wildbiodiversity/ws_kws.html Tamil Nadu Forest Department] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080323053453/http://www.forests.tn.nic.in/WildBiodiversity/ws_kws.html |date=23 March 2008 }}. Forests.tn.nic.in. Retrieved on 2013-07-28.</ref> The forests of the district are administered through the Kanyakumari Forest Division, with headquarters at Nagercoil, the capital of Kanyakumari District.\n\n==Flora and fauna==\n\nThe flora and fauna of Kanyakumari District are vast and diverse. Kanyakumari district has 4 types of lands except Desert. In which, Forest has a significant place in the district's landscape. The district's forest areas were surrounded by plenty of rivers and falls. Forests also has significant mountainous landscape. The district has forests of 40239.55 [[Hectares]]. The district's forests are situated between Kalakkad Mundanthurai Tiger Reserve and [[Neyyar Wildlife Sanctuary|Neyyar]] Forests in [[Kerala]]. [[Kaalikesam]], [[Balamore]], [[Upper Kodayar]], [[Lower Kodayar]], [[Mukkadal]] are the important places in Forests.\n\n===Flora===\nThe forests in Kanyakumari District has numerous high trees and large plants. Especially, the Kanyakumari forests has highly grown [[Santalum album|sandal]] trees, [[teak]] trees, [[rosewood]] trees, [[Wild Jack]] trees. There are also plenty of [[Herbal medicine|herbal]] plants. These plants, if used properly, can cure many diseases. Several private estates are in the forests. [[Piper (plant)|pepper]] and [[cloves]] are grown in large numbers in such estates. Totally the district's forests has some 600 varieties of large trees and another 3500 varieties of small trees.{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n===Fauna===\nAnimals on the hills of the district include [[Bengal Tiger]], [[Leopard]], [[Elephant]], [[Sambar Deer]], [[Porcupine]]s, [[Indian Pangolin]]s and [[Wild Boar]]. while [[pied kingfisher]], [[painted stork]] and [[crane (bird)|cranes]] are commonly found in the water bodies and wetlands. Reptiles include [[monitor lizard]]s, [[pythonidae|pythons]], blood viper and other snakes.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\nIn Mahendragiri hills (about {{convert|4000|ft|m|abbr=on}} above sea level), one can find [[elephant]], [[tiger]], [[leopard]]s and [[deer]]. Leopard cubs often stray onto the highway near the hills and are sometimes run over by motorists.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\nThe Keeriparai and Maramalai hills are habitats for wild [[elephant]]s and [[Indian bison]]. The Kodayar hills are the breeding centers for the Indian rock pythons and Indian bison. In the Theroor wetlands, one can see several varieties of storks and migratory birds during specific seasons. [[Trout]] and other varieties of [[freshwater fish]] are found in the Pechiparai reservoir.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\nThe district also has a wildlife sanctuary and a bird sanctuary<ref name=\"GRUBH\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/yw/2003/02/01/stories/2003020101320300.htm|title=Sanctuary in the lowland plains|last=GRUBH|first=SHAILAJA ROBERT |date=1 February 2003|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2009-01-08|location=Chennai, India}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.kanyakumari.tn.nic.in Official Website of Kanyakumari district]\n* [http://www.kanyakumaridistrict.com About Kanyakumari district]\n\n{